TER.TERdecoder
Class ArgsParserDecoder

java.lang.Object
  TER.TERdecoder.ArgsParserDecoder

public class ArgsParserDecoder
extends java.lang.Object

Arguments parser for TER decoder. This class analyses a string of arguments and extract and check its validity. Usage example:
  construct
  [showArgsInfo]
  [get functions]

Version:
2.0
Author:
Group on Interactive Coding of Images (GICI)

Field Detail

argsSpecification

java.lang.String[][] argsSpecification
Arguments specificiation. The array describes argument, explain what is used and its default parameters. First index of array is argument; second specifies:
  • 0 - short argument specification (i.e. "-nl")
  • 1 - long argument specification (i.e. "--numberLevels")
  • 2 - parsing specification of argument ({} indicates mandatority, [] optionality)
  • 3 - default values
  • 4 - mandatory argument ("1") or non mandatory argument ("0")
  • 5 - explanation
